name: protein-glutamine gamma-glutamyltransferase
reaction: protein glutamine + alkylamine = protein N5-alkylglutamine + NH3 [RN:R03983]
comment: Requires Ca2+. The gamma-carboxamide groups of peptide-bound glutamine residues act as acyl donors, and the 6-amino-groups of protein- and peptide-bound lysine residues act as acceptors, to give intra- and inter-molecular N6-(5-glutamyl)-lysine crosslinks. Formed by proteolytic cleavage from plasma Factor XIII
